{
  "answer": "**Bachay ki Dua** (\"A Child's Prayer\") is the 16th poem (chapter) in Allama Iqbal's *Bang-E-Dara Part 1* (1924), a collection of Urdu poetry. Here's the English translation:[^1]\n\n> [p-a0420d] A Child's Prayer  \n> \n> [p-28b7ba] My deepest longing comes to my lips as a prayer:  \n> O God, may my life be like a candle's flare.  \n> \n> [p-4bb8de] May my life's spark dispel the darkness of the world,  \n> May my shining light in every place be unfurled.  \n> \n> [p-b049bf] May I become my homeland's grace and pride,  \n> Like a flower that adorns the garden-side.  \n> \n> [p-01b332] O Lord, let my life be a moth's in its desire,  \n> To love the candle of knowledge, and draw ever nigher.  \n> \n> [p-877b09] Let my life's work be to champion the poor,  \n> To love the weak, and those who sorrow endure.  \n> \n> [p-39abc8] My God! Protect me from all that is wrong,  \n> And guide me on the righteous path, where I belong.[^2]\n\nIn this poignant prayer, the child asks God for a selfless, illuminating life—like a candle that burns to light the world and dispel its darkness.[^3] They wish to bring honor to their homeland, like a flower beautifying a garden; to pursue knowledge with moth-like passion; to protect the poor and love the weak and suffering; and above all, for protection from evil and guidance on the path of righteousness.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, chapter 16 (\"Bachay Ki Dua\"), translation, [chapter](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Ibid., [full passage](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-a0420d).\n\n[^3]: Ibid., [p-28b7ba](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-28b7ba) and [p-4bb8de](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-4bb8de).\n\n[^4]: Ibid., [p-b049bf](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-b049bf), [p-01b332](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-01b332), [p-877b09](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-877b09), and [p-39abc8](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/16-bachay-ki-dua/translation/#p-39abc8).",
